 shows for their London, Paris and Santiago stops. On January 29, the eight-piece announced additional dates to their existing shows in Texas and Madrid, on top of new stops in Shizuoka in May and Rome in July.</p><p> Tickets to the newly added shows of Stray Kids&#39; tour in Texas, Madrid, Shizuoka and Rome are set to go on sale on February 5 at 3pm local time. Head to Live Nation for more information.</p><h2> <strong>The dates for Stray Kids&#39; 2024 to 2025 &#39;dominATE&#39; world tour are:</strong></h2><p> <strong>AUGUST 2024</strong><br /> <strong>24: Seoul, South Korea, KSPO Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>25: Seoul, South Korea, KSPO Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>31: Seoul, South Korea, KSPO Dome (FINISHED)</strong></p><p> <strong>SEPTEMBER 2024</strong><br /> <strong>01: Seoul, South Korea, KSPO Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>28: Singapore, Singapore, Singapore National Stadium (FINISHED)</strong></p><p> <strong>OCTOBER 2024</strong><br /> <strong>19: Melbourne, Victoria, Marvel Stadium (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>26: Sydney, New South Wales, Allianz Stadium (FINISHED)</strong></p><p> <strong>NOVEMBER 2024</strong><br /> <strong>02: Kaohsiung, Taiwan, Kaohsiung National Stadium (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>14: Tokyo, Japan, Tokyo Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>16: Tokyo, Japan, Tokyo Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>17: Tokyo, Japan, Tokyo Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>23: Manila, the Philippines, Philippine Arena (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>29: Macau, China, Galaxy Arena (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>30: Macau, China, Galaxy Arena (FINISHED)</strong></p><p> <strong>2024年12月</strong><br /><strong>05: Osaka, Japan, Kyocera Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>07: Osaka, Japan, Kyocera Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>08: Osaka, Japan, Kyocera Dome (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>14: Bangkok, Thailand, National Stadium (FINISHED)</strong><br /> <strong>21: Jakarta, Indonesia, Indo