chii-2025-Getty-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1392px) 100vw, 1392px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/doechii">Doechii</a> has released a new song titled &#39;Nosebleeds&#39; in celebration of her watershed <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/grammys">Grammy</a> win.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/doechii-alligator-bites-never-heal-review-3788938">Doechii – &#39;Alligator Bites Never Heal&#39; review: a candid sonic diary of struggle and resilience</a></strong></li></ul><p> The hip-hop artist won the coveted Best Rap Album at the awards ceremony last night (February 2) with her mixtape &#39;Alligator Bites Never Heal&#39;, beating out the likes of <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/eminem">Eminem</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/j-cole">J. Cole</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/future">Future</a> . Doechii&#39;s win also makes her the third female artist to receive the award after <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lauryn-hill">Lauryn Hill</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/cardi-b">Cardi B</a> .</p><p> Just hours after her televised win, Doechii dropped &#39;Nosebleeds&#39; as a ferocious victory lap, where she raps about showing up her naysayers. Per <a href="https://genius.com/34441758" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Genius</em></a> , she also references Kanye West&#39;s acceptance speech for when he won Rap Album of the Year in 2005 for &#39;The College Dropout&#39;.</p><p> “ <em>I don&#39;t know, is she gonna go crazy?她会发疯吗？ / Everyone wanted to know what Doechii would do if she didn&#39;t win / I guess we&#39;ll never—</em> “, she raps, riffing off of West&#39;s past words, which read: “He&#39;s gonna wild out, he&#39;s gonna do something crazy… Everybody want to know what I would do if I didn&#39;t win… I guess we&#39;ll never know.”</p><p> Listen to the track below. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Doechii - Nosebleeds (Audio)" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/AcIqoSLeATs?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Doechii was also nominated for Best New Artist, an award that went to <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/chappell-roan">Chappell Roan</a> , who used her stage time to <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grammys-2025-chappell-roans-best-new-artist-acceptance-speech-demands-record-labels-treat-their-artists-as-valuable-employees-3833896">advocate for up-and-coming artists to receive better treatment from major labels</a> . </p><div class="td_block_wrap tdb_single_content tdi_86 td-pb-border-top td_block_template_2 td-post-content tagdiv-type" data-td-block-uid="tdi_86" data-io-article-url="https://www.nme.com/news/music/prince-the-clash-and-frankie-valli-among-those-honoured-at-grammys-special-merit-awards-3833798"><div class="tdb-block-inner td-fix-index"><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kendrick-lamar">Kendrick Lamar</a> walked away as the biggest winner of the night, clinching five awards including Record of The Year and Song Of The Year for &#39;Not Like Us&#39;. He also took home the Grammys for Best Rap Performance and Best Rap Song for &#39;Not Like Us&#39;, which has also won Best Music Video. See the list of winners of the 2025 Grammys <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grammys-2025-see-the-full-list-of-winners-3833854">here</a> .</p></div></div><p> Even as Doechii won the award for Best Rap Album, the rapper and singer has yet to release her debut album. In December, she spoke about what it would look like, teasing that it will be released sometime this year.</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/doechii-reveals-she-is-releasing-her-debut-album-next-year-3820382">In a <em>Variety</em> interview</a> , Doechii explained that she created &#39;Alligator Bites Never Heal&#39; with “pure presence and creativity” and hoped to “carry that with all of my projects and have that mentality moving forward” – including her upcoming album, which will incorporate live instrumentation.</p><p> “All I can think about is this album,” she said, “so I&#39;m just looking forward to making more hits, making more music and achieving more of my goals.就是这样。”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/doechii-drops-new-song-nosebleeds-in-celebration-of-grammy-win-3833956">Doechii drops new song &#39;Nosebleeds&#39; in celebration of Grammy win</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
