for her leading roles in hit dramas such as <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/daily-dose-of-sunshine">Daily Dose of Sunshine</a></em> and <em>Doom At Your Service,</em> portrays Kim Mu-bee.</p><p> <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/films/love-and-leashes">Love and Leashes</a> &#39;</em> Lee Jun-young and <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/parasyte-the-grey">Parasyte: The Grey</a> &#39;s</em> Jeon So-nee also join the supporting cast as as Hong Si-jun and Son Ju-ah, respectively. Si-jun is described as a genius but unknown songwriter, while Ju-ah is a screenwriter on the series.</p><p> Other actors who will appear in <em>Melo Movie</em> also include <em>Crazy Love&#39;s</em> Kim Jae-wook and <em>Night Has Come&#39;s</em> Cha Woo-min. The K-drama<em> </em>was penned by <em>Our Beloved Summer</em> screenwriter Lee Na-eun and helmed by director Oh Choong-hwan, known for his acclaimed work on <em>Hotel Del Luna</em> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/castaway-diva"><em>Castaway Diva</em></a> .</p><h2> Is there a trailer for Netflix&#39;s <em>Melo Movie</em> ?</h2><p> Netflix dropped the official trailer for <em>Melo Movie</em> on January 31. It begins with Go-gyeom asking over clips of himself and Mu-bee together, “You know when you get that gut feeling?” The trailer then shows the moment he first confessed to her as teens, however the moment quickly sours when Mu-bee reveals that he disappeared the morning after. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Melo Movie |官方预告片| Netflix" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/F4leB_jBpDk?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> On January 17, Netflix dropped the first teaser for <em>Melo Movie.</em> The clip starts with Go-gyeom and Mu-bee&#39;s rough first encounters with each other in a rural South Korean town, which leads to an unlikely friendship and eventual romance between the pair.</p><p> Despite their chemistry, they lose contact with each other as they enter adulthood. When Mu-bee makes her directorial debut, she is unwittingly reunited with film critic Go-gyeom, making them enemies once more. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Melo Movie |官方预告片| Netflix" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/o77FN86e-kU?start=5&enablejsapi=1#038;feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><h2> How to watch the new Netflix K-drama series? </h2><div class="td_block_wrap tdb_single_content tdi_86 td-pb-border-top td_block_template_2 td-post-content tagdiv-type" data-td-block-uid="tdi_86" data-io-article-url="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/netflixs-the-8-show-cast-plot-premiere-date-and-all-you-need-to-know-2-3617835"><div class="tdb-block-inner td-fix-index"><p> The new Netflix K-drama <em>Melo Movie</em> will make its premiere February 14 exclusively on Netflix.</p></div></div><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/melo-movie-netflix-k-drama-teaser-cast-plot-more-choi-woo-sik-park-bo-young-3830263">Watch the trailer for Netflix&#39;s &#39;Melo Movie&#39;, starring Choi Woo-sik and Park Bo-young</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
