 as a tribute to Los Angeles in the wake of the devastating wildfires earlier this year.</p><p> During a commercial break of the awards broadcast, the &#39;Abracadabra&#39; music video made its premiere. Harking back to the dark electro-pop of her career-highlight 2011 album &#39;Born This Way&#39;, the clip sees Gaga strike out in choreography with a group of dancers, all dressed in gothic attire.观看下面的音乐视频。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Lady Gaga -Abracadabra（官方音乐视频）" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vBynw9Isr28?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Standing in contrast to the R&amp;B ballad of &#39;Die With A Smile&#39;, Gaga previously said that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-describes-new-album-mayhem-as-utter-chaos-3832657">&#39;Mayhem&#39; will present “utter chaos” in terms of genre</a> – saying that its influences span from “&#39;90s alternative, electro-grunge, Prince and Bowie melodies, guitar and attitude, funky bass lines, French electronic dance, and analog synths.” &#39;Mayhem&#39; is available for pre-order <a href="https://www.ladygaga.com/us-en/shop/collections/mayhem" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> .</p><p> Comprised of 14 tracks executively produced by Gaga, Michael Polansky and Andrew Watt and featuring producers such as Cirkut and Gesaffelstein, &#39;Mayhem&#39; has been promised to reinvent Gaga&#39;s “early sound with a kaleidoscopic approach”, as per a press release.</p><p> For the Grammys this year, comedian Trevor Noah returned to host the event for the fifth consecutive year as <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/beyonce">Beyoncé</a> led the way with 11 nominations, making her <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/beyonce-is-now-officially-the-most-nominated-artist-in-grammy-history-3811696">the most nominated artist in the awards&#39; history</a> – she won the biggest award of the night, Album Of The Year, for &#39;Cowboy Carter&#39;, marking her first win in the category.</p><p> Kendrick Lamar walked away as the biggest winner of the night, clinching five awards including Record of The Year and Song Of The Year for &#39;Not Like Us&#39;. He also took home the Grammys for Best Rap Performance and Best Rap Song for &#39;Not Like Us&#39;, which has also won Best Music Video. See the full list of winners <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grammys-2025-see-the-full-list-of-winners-3833854">here</a> .</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-the-gothic-music-video-for-lady-gagas-surprise-new-single-abracadabra-3833942">Watch the gothic music video for Lady Gaga&#39;s surprise new single &#39;Abracadabra&#39;</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
